# truncating VGG16 at last layer before classification

class VGG16relu7(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self):
        super(VGG16relu7, self).__init__()
        vgg16 = models.vgg16(weights=weights)
        # Copy the entire convolutional part
        self.features = nn.Sequential( *list(vgg16.features.children()))
        # Keep a piece of the classifier:-2 to stop at relu7
        self.classifier = nn.Sequential(*list(vgg16.classifier.children())[:-2])
    
    def forward(self, x):
        x = self.features(x)
        x = x.view(x.size(0),-1)
        x = self.classifier(x)
        return x
In[8]:
PRINT_INTERVAL = 50
CUDA = True

def get_dataset(batch_size, path):

    # This function expands 3 times a gray level image
    # to transform it into an image RGB. Use it with transform.Lambda
    def duplicateChannel(img):
        img = img.convert('L')
        np_img = np.array(img, dtype=np.uint8)
        np_img = np.dstack([np_img, np_img, np_img])
        img = Image.fromarray(np_img)
        return img
    def resizeImage(img):
      return img.resize((224,224), Image.BILINEAR)

    #####################
    ## YOUR CODE HERE  ##
    #####################
    # Add pre-processing
    mu = torch.Tensor([0.485, 0.456, 0.406])
    sigma = torch.Tensor([0.229, 0.224, 0.225])

    train_dataset = datasets.ImageFolder(path+'/train',
        transform=transforms.Compose([ # Pre-processing TODO: 
            transforms.Lambda(duplicateChannel), 
            transforms.Lambda(resizeImage), 
            transforms.ToTensor(), 
            transforms.Normalize(mu, sigma)
        ]))
    val_dataset = datasets.ImageFolder(path+'/test',
        transform=transforms.Compose([ # Pre-processing TODO: 
            transforms.Lambda(duplicateChannel), 
            transforms.Lambda(resizeImage), 
            transforms.ToTensor(), 
            transforms.Normalize(mu, sigma)
        ]))
    ####################
    ##      END        #
    ####################

    train_loader = torch.utils.data.DataLoader(train_dataset,
                        batch_size=batch_size, shuffle=False, pin_memory=CUDA, num_workers=2)
    val_loader = torch.utils.data.DataLoader(val_dataset,
                        batch_size=batch_size, shuffle=False, pin_memory=CUDA, num_workers=2)

    return train_loader, val_loader

def extract_features(data, model):

    # data is a DataLoader
    # model is a model that takes an image and outputs a latent representation of the image 
    
    #####################
    ## YOUR CODE HERE  ##
    #####################
    # init features matrices
    X = []
    y = []
    ####################
    ##      END        #
    ####################

    for i, (input, target) in enumerate(data):
        if i % PRINT_INTERVAL == 0:
            print('Batch {0:03d}/{1:03d}'.format(i, len(data)))
        if CUDA:
            input = input.cuda()
        #####################
        ## YOUR CODE HERE  ##
        #####################

        
        # we convert the data from pytorch to numpy since the classification will be done with LinearSVC
        features = model(input) 
        features = features.cpu().detach().numpy()
        labels = target.detach().numpy()

        X.append(features)
        y.append(labels)
        
        ####################
        ##      END        #
        ####################

    X = np.concatenate(X, axis=0)  # shape: (N, 4096)
    y = np.concatenate(y, axis=0)  # shape: (N,)
    
    return X, y


def DatasetPrep(path="15SceneData", batch_size=8):

    print('Instanciation de VGG16relu7')
    #####################
    ## YOUR CODE HERE  ##
    #####################
    # Remplacer par le modle par un rseau tronqu pour faire de la feature extraction
    # On crera une nouvelle classe VGG16relu7 ici
    model = VGG16relu7()
    ####################
    ##      END        #
    ####################

    model.eval()
    if CUDA: # si on fait du GPU, passage en CUDA
        cudnn.benchmark = True
        model = model.cuda()

    # On rcupre les donnes
    print('Rcupration des donnes')
    train, test = get_dataset(batch_size, path)

    # Extraction des features
    print('Feature extraction')
    X_train, y_train = extract_features(train, model)
    X_test, y_test = extract_features(test, model)

    return X_train, y_train, X_test, y_test, train, test

def SVM_train_test(X_train, y_train, X_test, y_test, C = 1.0):
    #####################
    ## Votre code ici  ##
    #####################
    # Apprentissage et valuation des SVM  faire

    print('Apprentissage des SVM')
    SVM = LinearSVC(max_iter=5000, C = C)
    SVM.fit(X_train, y_train)
    
    accuracy = SVM.score(X_test, y_test)
        
    ####################
    ##      FIN        #
    ####################
    print('Accuracy = %f' % accuracy)

    return accuracy

Replacing the SVM classifier by a fully connected layer

In[13]:
# SVM -> FCL

class VGG16CLassHeadReplace(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self):
        super(VGG16CLassHeadReplace, self).__init__()
        
        vgg16 = models.vgg16(weights=weights)
        
        # Copy the entire convolutional part
        self.features = nn.Sequential( *list(vgg16.features.children()))
        
        # Keep a piece of the classifier:-2 to stop at relu7
        self.classifier = nn.Sequential(*list(vgg16.classifier.children())[:-2])
        
        # new classification head
        self.new_head = nn.Linear(4096, 15)
        
    def forward(self, x):
        x = self.features(x)
        x = x.view(x.size(0),-1)
        x = self.classifier(x)
        x = self.new_head(x)
        return x
In[48]:
# initialization of the model

print('Instanciation de VGG16CLassHeadRep')
model = VGG16CLassHeadReplace()


if CUDA: # si on fait du GPU, passage en CUDA
    cudnn.benchmark = True
    model = model.cuda()

for p in model.features.parameters():
    p.requires_grad = False

for p in model.classifier.parameters():
    p.requires_grad = False

for p in model.new_head.parameters():
    p.requires_grad = True


# training loop

criterion = torch.nn.CrossEntropyLoss()
optimizer = torch.optim.Adam(model.new_head.parameters(), lr=1e-4)
model.train()
epochs = 10

for j in range(epochs):
    
    print(f"---------Training Epoch {j}---------")
    
    for i, (input, target) in enumerate(train):
    
        if CUDA:
            input = input.cuda()
            target = target.cuda()
        
        output = model(input)
        loss = criterion(output, target)
    
        optimizer.zero_grad()
        loss.backward()
        optimizer.step()

# testing loop
corr = 0
print_step = 100
model.eval()
for i, (input, target) in enumerate(test):

    if i % print_step == 0:
        print(f"---------Evaluation Batch {i}---------")
    
    if CUDA:
        input = input.cuda()
        target = target.cuda()
    
    output = model(input)
    prediction = output.argmax(dim=1)

    corr += (prediction == target).sum().item()
